[normal]1.2.[bold]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal] 
[normal]Persistence with this unbalanced approach to low carbon innovation has the potential to accelerate carbon leakage and drive production
[normal] and jobs 
[normal]that 
[normal]are
[normal] 
[normal]essential 
[normal]to low carbon innovation, 
[normal]abroad.
[normal]1.3.[bold]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal] 
[normal]Low carbon innovation opportunities exist in industry
[normal] but 
[normal]UK 
[normal]manufacturing requires a certain 
[normal]well-crafted
[normal] 
[normal]green policy 
[normal]agenda that is synergistic with its manufacturing and industrial polic
[normal]ies
[normal] in order to assist
[normal] long term investments.
[normal]1.4.[bold]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal] 
[normal]For funding 
[normal]of
[normal] low carbon innovation to 
[normal]be successful
[normal], the UK 
[normal]must
[normal] 
[normal]ensure that carbon
[normal],
[normal] production
[normal] and 
[normal]jobs 
[normal]leakage is minimized.
[normal] By supporting low carbon 
[normal]manufacturing industry
[normal] the
[normal] UK 
[normal]Government can achieve the 
[normal]twin 
[normal]benefit to the 
[normal]environment and the economy.
[normal]1.5.[bold]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal] 
[normal]To date the 
[normal]UK Government 
[normal]low carbon support 
[normal]policy has concentrated on giving power generators certainty so that this sector is able to carry out low risk investment in renewable energy
[normal] via its guaranteed subsidies
[normal]. Industry 
[normal]is not afforded the same privilege and in addition has to bear the pass through cost of the certainty afforded to the power generators.
[normal] 
[normal]Government
[normal] must
[normal] provide
[normal] 
[normal]the same balance of 
[normal]incentives and funding 
[normal]across
[normal] all sectors
[normal] of the economy
[normal].
[normal]1.6.[bold]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal] 
[normal]S
[normal]ectors like cement and lime where plant lasts around 35-40 years, 
[normal]need
[normal] long term certainty to attract investment. 
[normal]Up to now industry has been a missed
[normal] opportunity for UK Government
[normal]’s
[normal] 
[normal]low carbon benefits
[normal]. Now would be the ideal time to put some of the low 
[normal]carbon innovation underspend to good use in this sector.
[normal]1.7.[bold]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal] 
[normal]Considerable work is required to make the UK an attractive place to invest. This can only be achieved through
[normal] the
[normal] provision of incentives to attract investment and 
[normal]the 
[normal]minimiz
[normal]ation of
[normal] the cumulative
[normal] burden of climate change and energy policies on industry.
